ZH: 我今天买了一条新鲜的香肠。
EN: I bought a fresh sausage today.

ZH: 这个香肠味道很好。
EN: This sausage tastes very good.

ZH: 我喜欢用香肠来做早餐。
EN: I like to use sausage for breakfast.

ZH: 香肠是一种常见的早餐食物。
EN: Sausage is a common breakfast food.

ZH: 他偏爱熏香肠。
EN: He prefers smoked sausages.

ZH: 这种香肠很辣。
EN: This sausage is very spicy.

ZH: 那家餐馆的烤香肠很有名。
EN: The grilled sausages at that restaurant are famous.

ZH: 我们家常备一些肉香肠。
EN: We always have some meat sausage at home.

ZH: 香肠是德国的传统美食。
EN: Sausage is a traditional German delicacy.

ZH: 这款香肠我吃过，味道不错。
EN: I have tried this sausage, it tastes good.

ZH: 香肠一般是由肉类做成的。
EN: Sausage is usually made from meat.

ZH: 他的早餐里有烤土豆和炒香肠。
EN: His breakfast includes grilled potatoes and fried sausages.

ZH: 她准备了一盘香肠和芝士。
EN: She prepared a plate of sausages and cheese.

ZH: 这种香肠的口感很好。
EN: This sausage has a good texture.

ZH: 他们的意大利香肠很受欢迎。
EN: Their Italian sausages are popular.

ZH: 香肠可以准备成多种口味。
EN: Sausages can be prepared in many flavors.

ZH: 他喜欢在沙拉里加入一些切成小块的香肠。
EN: He likes to add some diced sausages to his salad.

ZH: 这家店有各式各样的香肠供选择。
EN: This shop has a variety of sausages to choose from.

ZH: 生香肠需要足够长的时间来腌制。
EN: Fresh sausages need enough time to marinate.
